column6: Built in 1981, the VECHAAR (Vishalla Environmental Centre for Heritage of Art, Architecture and Research) Utensils Museum is an effort to cherish and preserve Gujarat’s rich culinary heritage and traditional artistic skills of its craftsmen.  #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/5hcRehsuEh

Auto World Vintage Car Museum in Ahmedabad is dedicated to a world-class collection of vintage cars, antique vehicles, utility vehicles, motorcycles, and medieval buggies.#MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/0iFNLRUKfq

The Vande Mataram Memorial is a unique national monument seeking to immortalise the key episodes in India’s struggle for freedom from British Rule. #MusuemsofGujarat #VisitGujarat http://bit.ly/2tZaQPc  pic.twitter.com/Ck5lPjYfE6

Maharaja Fatesingh Museum was established in the year 1961, as a school for the Maharaja’s children and later was converted into a museum. This museum has a varied collection of artefacts, works of art collected by Maharaja during his trips abroad and much more. #MuseumsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/0MqTbtrZJi

Wankaner museum near Rajkot, showcases the grandeur of old Kathiawar through royal belongings like shields, swords, duelling pistols, linen chests, portraits, paintings, thrones, silver plated howdahs. #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/ZbxNi20DDl

Shyamji Krishna Varma Memorial was built to pay a tribute to the contribution of Shyamji Krishna Varma in India’s freedom struggle. Exhibits, documentaries & films inspire the present and future generations. #MusuemsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/LfrL2ktSOu

Gujarat has always been one of the most wonderful tourist places in India. At the foot of Shatrunjaya Hills, this museum dedicated to Jain heritage & culture, houses an excellent collection of Jain artefacts, excavated idols from earlier temples & much more.  #MuseumsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/XVFrlaSxbs

The beautiful museum celebrates the glorious crafts heritage of Kutch. Over forty distinct hand embroidery styles of Kutch, practiced by 12 different communities are on display here.  visit-  http://bit.ly/2FPfxQj #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/VEMVTuD1ru

Lakhota Palace in Jamnagar is a beautiful palace in the middle of Lakhota lake, built by the king Jam Ranmaliji. Lakhota Palace of yore is now transformed into a museum that houses relics of medieval times.#MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat http://bit.ly/2FKPDx5  pic.twitter.com/QgZEpeKtPA

Visit this place & get introduced to the lifestyle, costumes, heritage & ecology of the Dang tribe. This place provides learning about many major forms of tribal expression such as a stone funerary column, grass ornaments, stuffed birds, wood carving,,etc. #MuseumsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/BwFUez3O1K

Lothal is one of the best sites to see the urban planning of the Indus Valley Civilization (2600–1900 BC) .Allow yourself to be transported to an era 4,500 years ago, & see in your mind’s eye, a thriving port. #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/mgXPcwxYdz

The Lalbhai Dalpatbhai Institute of Indology in Ahmedabad is a humble abode where it conserves, nurtures and protects history in its womb and makes it come alive for the present generation.  #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/irK35BAr3g

The oldest museum in Gujarat, founded in 1877 by Maharao Khengarji, it has the largest existing collection of Kshatrapa inscriptions, dating to the 1st century AD, as well as examples of the extinct Kutchi script & an interesting collection of old coins. #MuseumsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/XT9tFRo4iQ

Bharatiya Sanskriti Darshan is a museum built by a scholar, Ramsinhji K Rathod to exhibit the folk art of Kutch. The museum exhibits an excellent collection of Kutchi folk art and crafts, especially from the more remote regions of the district.. #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/nuHgPMCSsR

Darbar Hall Museum is situated in the heart of the Junagadh City. This museum displays weaponry such as the stick gun and 'tiger nails', Jamnagar daggers, armours, etc. Revisit the royal era of Nawabs of Junagadh.  #MusuemsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/tfWnmMQmMj

Dandi Kutir is a historical landmark & a museum created in Gujarat’s capital, Gandhinagar. It is one of a kind, three-layered architecture that is used to narrate the life of Gandhi with the modern technology to give an , immersive & spellbinding experience.  #MusuemsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/SInQqO1Yca

Alpana Heritage Museum is built in Gujarati Haveli style with traditional carvings in rich teakwood. This haveli cum museum is owned by Gujarati business family and their love for preserving heritage can be observed during your visit here.. #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/8gPvfnA56A

Established in April 1977, the Shreyas Folk Museum pays a tribute to the indefatigable spirit of the Gujarati women, who have added remarkable value to the Gujarati heritage with their soulful crafts and unbound imagination. #WomensDay #Gujarat #MusuemsofGujarat pic.twitter.com/8Ki8ajtzqW

Sharad Baug Museum was once the residence of Madansingh, the last king of Kutch. This Italian style mansion set in spacious & marvelously tended gardens was opened to the public in the year 1991 as a museum.   http://bit.ly/2FqoxaU #MuseumsofGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/Jx69e4RFsY

Riverside Palace/Orchard Palace at Gondal is one of the most guest-friendly hotels in Gujarat. The Riverside Palace/Orchard Palace equipped with 7 double bedrooms at the Orchard palace and 11 double bedrooms at the Riverside Palace. #VisitGujarat #HeritageHotels pic.twitter.com/7Q81kHxoFk

Gujarat welcomes all filmmakers to come and explore the picture-perfect destinations in the Most Film-Friendly State of India! #CinematicTourism #VisitGujarat #IndianCinema #Gujarat https://youtu.be/Ll1mHw-iMbU

A quaint Heritage hotel situated in a small town Gondal in Gujarat with an old world charm and ancient staff, reminiscent of a bygone era of Maharajas and their ways. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/1eaRdJyaq5

Constructed in the late 1920s, Balaram Palace was the weekend retreat and hunting resort of the Lohanis who ruled from Jalore in southwestern Rajasthan. It can now become your retreat too! #HeritageHotels pic.twitter.com/SEiw75YD1M

Balaram Palace Resort, once the hunting retreat of the Lohani Nawab of Palanpur, is now a Heritage Classic hotel. We welcome you to this opulent 13 acres of terraced upland with a hotel rising from a hilly stream & surrounded by lush green gardens. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/vInqR26rza

The reasons for the immense popularity of Bhavani Villa- Danta is the majestic environment & warm hospitality. For nature lovers, the hotel is an ideal retreat. Surrounded by the Aravalli Range, this royal property offers a stay that leaves a lasting impressing #HeritageHotels pic.twitter.com/VtaRgapdrM

Danta was an 895  http://sq.km  princely State ruled by Parmars, descendants of the great King of Ujjain. With the oldest part of the house as old as 150 years, a stay in the Bhavani Villa Danta Palace can turn out to be extremely exciting. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/dVOsePNO1s

This #WorldWildlifeDay, with the theme of Save #BigCats, Gujarat is proud to showcase Sasan Gir National Park which has successfully conserved the Asiatic lions to raise their population to 650. Visit Sasan Gir. Visit the Asiatic Lions in their natural habitat. #Gujarat pic.twitter.com/ZepsnO9h0t

Dowlat Villas Palace is a great heritage getaway for travellers across the world to experience the royal living. It has beautiful gothic style pillared balconies, attractive courtyards, open terraces, a lovely garden and comfortable rooms with antique furnishings. #HeritageHotels pic.twitter.com/MMLGOOw38Z

Kadval Darbar Ghad shares its legacy with all who wish to experience and have a taste of this royal luxury. Discover countless secrets of the centuries past while you explore nature trails. For more details -  http://www.gujarattourism.com/hotel/details/1131 …#HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/uE2ty0ePCo

Kadval Darbar Gadh was built in the reign of Late Thakoresaheb Bharat Singhji in the year 1897 and has been maintained and preserved ever since.  #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/gnRfOneuqb

A boutique heritage hotel with 21 rooms and suites providing an experience of a bygone era and yet equipped with modern facilities. The vision of the property is to preserve the rich cultural heritage associated to a Gujarati ancestral home. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/16mICSL2yM

Tushar Dalal grandson of Manibhai Dalal continues the legacy and has thoughtfully and carefully restored the property and has left it open for the tourist to experience the old charm of his ancestral House. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/2k2hw0WmJC

'A Home for Nature lovers' is a name that perfectly suits Jambughoda palace. A Home for Nature Lovers has 20 non-airconditioned & air-conditioned suites & rooms. Come here to stay in a property that is more than a century old & spread across 100 acres of greenery.#VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/vbevIoP1g7

Travel back more than a century, in to 100 acres of sheer hypnotic greenery and enter the Jambughoda Palace now converted into A Home for Nature Lovers – a heritage hotel in Jambughoda, near Vadodara in Gujarat. #HeritageHotels #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/VUeILWx5Rc
India's 1st World Heritage City Ahmedabad, celebrates its 608th Foundation Day on 26 February, 2018. #Ahmedabad #WorldHeritageCity#HappyBirthdayAhmedabad pic.twitter.com/rscLHpLzPQ

When you visit Gir, you are visiting one of the largest deciduous forests of the world & the only wild habitat of the Asiatic Lion. It is also home to 280 bird species & the rare Chowsingha antelope! Great photo opportunities await you here. #PristineGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/tUMbmCfkYQ

Thol Lake is a small but scenic lake, surrounded by marshes, scrub forest and farmlands. Explore more about the Thol lake bird sanctuary  here -  http://bit.ly/1iA35UW  #PristineGujarat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/A0p7jHJAEK

Nalsarovar is a bird watcher's delight! It is one of the largest bird sanctuaries in India. In winters, the sanctuary sees flocks of indigenous and migratory birds, with as many as 250 species passing through.  http://bit.ly/2EEPqvJ  #PristineGujarat #Wildlife pic.twitter.com/8xE4l1CCpt
First-Ever Conference on Photo Tourism in India, Live from White Rann Resort Dhordo, Kutch, Gujarat. http://bit.ly/2op1cPJ #PhotoTourism #Gujarat

If you’ve always dreamed of visiting the African savannah, but haven’t quite managed to take the trip, a journey through Saurashtra may help satiate your wanderlust. Visit Velavadar Blackbuck, National Park.   http://bit.ly/2oco4Tf  #PristineGujarat #Wildlife pic.twitter.com/R0MLc9TCTn

The Indian Wild Ass  Wildlife Sanctuary, spread across nearly 5000 sq km of the Little Rann  is home to the endangered species, locally known as the Ghudkar -  http://bit.ly/2Cyl8o9  #PristineGujarat #Wildlife pic.twitter.com/z0FTnS0fl5

Whether you are a birder, a wildlife enthusiast, or just want to see the beauty of nature, Gujarat is a definite destination for any photographer. Come, experience and capture the serenity and beauty of the wilderness like never before #VisitGujarat #LiveWhatYouLove pic.twitter.com/SclWeRgwmp
Come, visit Gujarat Tourism stall (TGCL) at Travel and Tourism Fair 2018 at  Bengaluru! #TravelTradeFair2018 pic.twitter.com/m61YEyThgr

Balasinor also known as Vadasinor, was established during the 18th century as a princely state of Nawab Babi or Yusufzai Pathan Dynasty. You get to stay in their Garden retreat that has been converted into a heritage hotel. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/0alfMVMKQc

Shutterbugs embark on a breathtaking journey through enchanting flora & fauna of Gujarat with renowned wildlife photographer, Sanat Shodhan #LiveWhatYouLove #VisitGujarat #Wildlife #Photography @timesofindia pic.twitter.com/4zRlKgxi5a

Do you know what a Pangolin is? Most people don’t! It is the most trafficked wild animal in the world, with more than 1 million Pangolins poached since 2000. On #WorldPangolinDay, let’s spread awareness of their existence & vulnerability. pic.twitter.com/cl0Dm8bri5
Watch Sankara unfold his journey to the colourful land of Kutch #VisitGujarat https://youtu.be/UZddWkcfxg0

'Times Passion Trails is a unique travel experience by @timesofindia which will help you actualize your passion for photography. Shutterbugs come along on a breathtaking journey through enchanting flora & fauna of Gujarat #LiveWhatYouLove http://bit.ly/2sAntiU

Gomati Sangam Ghat is the sacred place where Gomati River flows into the sea. Swarga Dwar of the Dwarkadish Temple takes you down to this ghat with just 56 steps. A bath in the river here is believed to have spiritual and healing merit. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/BClgHsh46B

Bangdi Bazaar is one of the oldest markets in Rajkot. Here, you can find a vast array of embroidered fabrics, bandhnis, bangles, beadworks, and readymade garments in a riot of colours & variety. Be mesmerised with the wares on display. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/XWyAiH4ii4

Gopnath Beach is an ideal tourist destination, located on the Gulf of Khambat. It is known for its pristine beauty and the coast is surrounded by tiny islands offering a picturesque delight from the beach, especially during sunset. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/i3fMc7Xuur

The Calico Museum of Textiles was inspired by the pioneering art historian and philosopher Dr. Ananda Coomaraswamy. The museum stands as a testimony to the rich textile heritage of India with its incredible collection of fabrics from the 15th Century. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/Cpj6KdekOb

Prag Mahal in Bhuj is an Italian Gothic style structure built in the late 19th century with Italian marble and sandstone brought from Rajasthan. Corinthian pillars around the palace adds to the charm. This exotic palace is must see. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/TcrONp37Vd

Each Copper Bell from Kutch rings a true story about the centuries-old coppersmithing techniques. Read here-  http://traveltalesfromindia.in/2018/01/the-copper-bell-house-at-nirona-the-extraordinary-crafts-village-of-kutch-gujarat/ … via @mridulablog
Outlook Traveller, Sheetal Vyas unfolds her journey to the calm, charismatic and enigmatic Rann of Kutch. #VisitGujarat #IncredibleKutch https://tinyurl.com/ybgb2smt

One of the 14 Ashokan Rock Edict from 250 BC can be seen in Junagadh. This rock edict is a huge stone with carvings in Brahmi script in Pali language which talks of the Buddhist way of life propagated by Ashoka. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/mVzfzDTV6b

A true replica of the original Vaishno Devi Mandir of Jammu Kashmir can be spotted in Ahmedabad. Thousands of devotees and tourists visit to this popular temple every year. Take a tour! #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/eB1h34hD6R
#Gujarat is the #TOP most among the fastest growing state in tourism sector. #VisitGujarat #Tourism http://www.millenniumpost.in/features/gujarat-serving-dessert-in-desert-for-tourists-283087 …

Around 3500 majestic and marvellous Blackbucks reside in the  forest of Velvadar near Bhavnagar. This incredible sight was captured by Mr Pradip Shejul during his visit to the Blackbuck National Park, Velavadar. Come & witness the beauty in the wilderness. #Velvadar #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/Tjd5bg7XF3

Scour through colonial-styles lamps, art decors, vintage crockery, coins, furniture and many more. The Shanivari or Saturday Market near Makai Pul is one of the largest flea markets in Gujarat, selling antiques, trinkets and old furniture. #VisitSurat #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/MZBkAC1k58

The Naulakha Palace, which translates to 'nine lakhs', gets its name from the amount of money incurred in constructing the palace. This is one of the oldest palaces in Gujarat and is an architectural gem! Pay a visit to Gondal to see this beauty! #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/Bt6v3M0mXx

Poshina, in Sabarkantha district is home to a tribal shrine where you find the staggering scene of thousands of terracotta horses standing in rows as offerings to the local goddess.  #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/fGNN01WTSc

One exceptional temple in India which is dedicated to Sudama, who is said to be a childhood friend of Lord Krishna. Don’t miss out on exploring this temple & its architecture during your visit to Porbandar. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/mi0v0lbKmu
We are happy to announce the winner of #SkyInGujarat Kite flying photography contest! We'd like to say a big thanks to all the participants. pic.twitter.com/9xXOSYQp1B

Multiple-award-winning Salvi family has been safeguarding the tradition of weaving double ikat & keeping this heritage alive for centuries which is famous as Patola of Patan today. They have a museum dedicated to the art of weaving ikat/patola, which is a must see. #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/URtsZCN1e1
Celebrate the glory of IndiaOne flag. One land. One people. #Republicday2018 pic.twitter.com/wZtKPlpLqq

Marine National Park & Sanctuary in the Gulf of Kutch, at Jamnagar, proffers exotic sightings and fascinating underwater life experiences. It is the first Marine National Park of India where you can spot rich marine & bird life. Plan your weekend visit, now! #VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/HHABEgH4HS

Bird watchers have been rejoicing in the pink paradise that Gujarat is now, with flocks of beautiful flamingos. Come and visit these pink beauties soon. #VisitGujarat #FlamingosPhoto Credit- Pradip Shejul. pic.twitter.com/bllRpGvh00

Polo Utsav brings you an opportunity to spend your holidays in beautiful cottages surrounded by hills and lush green forest area. Take a ride around nature to explore the goodness nature has to offer, from 20th November’17 to 20th February’18. #PoloUtsav#VisitGujarat pic.twitter.com/USy8F2icCz

If you are a connoisseur of music and dance, you must attend Uttarardh Mahotsav, a two-day festival, to get an ethereal experience. Gear yourself this weekend, to experience the essence of classical Indian dance and music. #incredibleindia #Gujarat #Modhera pic.twitter.com/SZy03vY17S

Law Garden in the centre of Ahmedabad, bustles with shopaholics & foodies every evening. The atmosphere is festive with crowds around stalls or “lorries”, selling traditional and latest fashion clothes along with tasty, yummy street food for the shoppers. #Mustvisit #Gujarat pic.twitter.com/CyeTgL9mSA

Thank you for your interest in the #SkyInGujarat Kite flying photography contest. We have closed the entries for this year's contest. Sorry we can't take in any more entries!Our esteemed judges will evaluate the best photo and announce the winner on 20th Jan

Blackbuck are strikingly handsome animals with long, spiral horns marked with rings and distinctly streaked faces with white patches around their eyes. Blackbuck National Park, Velavadar is a tiny haven for the Blackbucks. #GujaratTourism #Wildlife #wildlifeconservation pic.twitter.com/LGEF47t73v
Gujarat plans Wagah-type tourist attraction. Tourists wil be will be privileged to see the Beating Retreat border ceremony similar to the Wagh Border ceremony. http://bit.ly/2DnfERE

Participate in  Photo Contest by sharing your most stunning and beautiful kite flying pictures with us on Facebook & Instagram and stand a chance to win the contest. #SkyinGujarat #IKF2018 #PhotoContest #GujaratRead the Rules and Regulations here -   http://bit.ly/2qEju3H  pic.twitter.com/mIbvYvB5XR

This Uttarayan share your special moments with us and show the entire world the beauty and diversity with which Kite Festival is celebrated in Gujarat. Details about the Photo Contest will be shared at 9 PM tonight. #SkyinGujarat #IKF2018 #PhotoContest pic.twitter.com/dQtAD9lll4

The inauguration ceremony of International Kite Festival 2018 left all visitors at the Ahmedabad Riverfront amazed. Everyone witnessed myriad colours and emotions splashing though the skies. Here are some glimpses from the event for you. #SkyInGujarat #IKF2018 pic.twitter.com/VfgqHPAn16

The International Kite Festival is here! Get contest ready and stand a chance to win a gift voucher worth Rs. 5000. For more details, watch this space.#SkyinGujarat #IKF2018 #Gujarat #PhotoContest pic.twitter.com/gRAwTfU9b2

We cordially invite you all to grace the inauguration of the week-long celebration of International Kite Festival 2018. The inaugural function is organized in #Ahmedabad on 7th January and the fest will continue until 14th January'2018. pic.twitter.com/kd0lRqjWz8
We are ready to declare a Photo contest soon. Get, Set, Shoot. #SkyinGujarat #IKF2018 #GujaratTourism pic.twitter.com/JIUd86lcHu

Chhari means salt affected and Dhandh means Shallow wet-lands. Chhari Dhandh place is a paradise for bird watchers and ornithologists, having around 370 bird species and is particularly rich in rapports, water fly, waders and larks. #GujaratTourism #Birdwatching #NatureLover pic.twitter.com/qEGpoz5AG5

#Chikki is an addictive, easy-to-make treat. It is a popular snack made of groundnuts, sesame seeds and puffed rice in melted jiggery. Gorge on them in winters to keep your body warm. #GujaratTourism #WinterSpecial #EnergyBar pic.twitter.com/DMv8y3cEu4

#RannUtsav is in its liveliest form during the #FullMoon. Hundreds of lucky tourists witnessed the White Rann illuminated by beautiful moon rays, creating a magical ambience. The last full moon of Rann of Kutch awaits your presence. Plan your #holidays now. #GujaratTourism pic.twitter.com/xAsRt9SDO5

Must eat street food in Surat - Surti Locho is a very delicious, simple and a healthy steamed snack. The dish derives its name from its loose, soft and mushy consistency. #GujaratTourism #LocalFood #GujaratiSpeciality #foodies #FoodFood pic.twitter.com/AhBlIp8vtA

Winters are made special for Gujaratis by the winter special millet called Ponk or Paunk. This green delight is used to make amazing warm winter snacks, especially the favourite limbu-mari ni sev (lemon and sev). #GujaratTourism #seasonalfood pic.twitter.com/kr11EoC97d
Life is a sum of experiences. So, resolve to travel to Gujarat in 2018 for unforgettable new experiences. Wishing you a very experiential 2018 #HappyNewYear pic.twitter.com/ufrZMCDkO2

Full moon nights at the Rann Utsav, are dates that cannot be missed. Be ready to witness an ocean of shining white sand with a large moon hanging low over the horizon for company. Surreal. Serene. Stupendous. #GujaratTourism #Kutch #RannUtsav pic.twitter.com/J1kh0oH7yc

Do you love #Birdwatching? Do spotting migratory birds excite you? This place is for you! Many migratory birds nest and breed in the lake and its periphery. The two most prominent species of birds recorded in the sanctuary are Flamingoes and Sarus crane. #Gujarat #GujaratToruism pic.twitter.com/jfPBkcsZlg

If twittering #birds call your heart to the great outdoors, plan your #holiday in Gujarat. With more than 600 bird species and extraordinary sightings, it’s a paradise for #birdwatchers. pic.twitter.com/JypfUftCXU

Be one with nature at #Gir National Park, the royal kingdom of #Asiaticlions & essentially the only place on earth where these majestic beasts roam free. Sasan Gir is the most celebrated wildlife sanctuary in India with 523 Asiatic lions living her in natural jungle settings. pic.twitter.com/3hBpPWJd6D

Ahmedabad is celebrating Kankaria Carnival 2017 from the 25th of December till the 31st of December. This Carnival on the shores of Kankaria lake continues for six days and nights. It will be a fun-filled week-long event, with programmes including sports, dance, cultural events. pic.twitter.com/1f6m9iRp7n

The much awaited International Kite Festival 2018 is here! The sky will come alive with kites in different colours, shapes and sizes, soaring high up making it vibrant. We welcome all to the World Heritage City Ahmedabad to join in this festival. pic.twitter.com/Sitrhx9eTi

Undhiyu is one of the most famous and must have Gujarati dish. It is a winter speciality and is traditional Gujarati mixed vegetable curry that will surely tickle your taste. #Winter #Gujaratsspecial pic.twitter.com/2ShLu52n9m

Nalsarovar Bird Sanctuary is a spectacular natural lake with shallow waters and muddy lagoons, dotted by 360 islets. It offers an ideal wintering ground for thousands of migratory birds.  #BirdWatching #GujaratTourism #Gujarat #NalSarovar pic.twitter.com/HkofknHW3A

The Panch Mahotsav - the celebration of culture. Panch Mahotsav celebrates the exquisite beauty & magnificence of the heritage, architecture, & culture of #Champaner & #Pavagadh. Join us to experience the unique  architectural marvels from 16th December 2017 to 15th January 2018. pic.twitter.com/w2uB3rhKmt

A unique Wildlife experience awaits you in Little Rann of Kutch! The Wild Ass Sanctuary located in Little Rann is the only place on earth where the endangered Indian Wild Ass, locally known as the Ghudkar still lives. #GujaratTourism pic.twitter.com/fuA4c5R7X3

Calico Museum of Textiles with its incredible collection of fabrics illustrating varied Indian handicraft textiles across five centuries is a celebrated Institute in Indian Textiles around the world. #GujaratHeritage pic.twitter.com/bVowbXbR2Y

Gujarat is a major producer of block prints in the country. Block printing is done using a hand carved woven block and mordant dyeing. The ‘Ajarakh’ resist printing of Dhamadka and Ajarakhpur in Kutch is very well known. #GujaratHandicrafts pic.twitter.com/DomFaS2ICw
